page.title: 12ECOLOGY.CLAPHAM RIVER BANK
page.content: On Wednesday the 26 June we went to the beck.It was a fine day but the water was cold and fast flowing because it had been raining the night before.In the water we saw flies,snails, and out of the water we saw ladybirds, duck eggs,midges, bees,and slugs,there are some mink and water rats but we didn't see any.Along the bank we saw different flowers,meadow buttercup,red clover,nettles,bush vetch,woody night shade,cuckoo flower,and celandines. There were sycamore,and ash trees by the beck,and there was a flowering cherry.We brought some insects back to school to identify then after a while we took them back.A few of the plants were "garden escapes"or just the seeds of a garden plant been blown out.
